1279
01:50:49,840 --> 01:50:51,239
...some sign of--

1280
01:50:51,480 --> 01:50:52,230
Stop it!

1281
01:50:53,760 --> 01:50:56,479
You'll never find
what you're looking for. Never.

1282
01:50:58,520 --> 01:51:00,078
You wanna know why.

1283
01:51:00,360 --> 01:51:02,430
And there is no why.

1284
01:51:19,240 --> 01:51:19,990
Don't.

1285
01:51:30,280 --> 01:51:34,068
If you check in, I'm heading for
the airport early. Meet me for coffee.

1286
01:51:36,200 --> 01:51:38,111
Hi, it's me. I'm running late.

1287
01:51:38,360 --> 01:51:41,750
There was something I needed to do.

1288
01:51:43,120 --> 01:51:46,749
Go without me. I'll get the next
plane and meet you at the hotel.

1289
01:51:48,360 --> 01:51:50,430
What are we doing? Do you know?

1290
01:52:13,360 --> 01:52:15,271
We made love that morning.

1291
01:52:19,440 --> 01:52:21,237
That's why she was late.

1292
01:53:33,120 --> 01:53:34,189
Get an ambulance!

1293
01:53:34,560 --> 01:53:35,788
I'm okay.

1294
01:53:36,200 --> 01:53:38,270
Get out of the car! Get out!

1295
01:53:39,360 --> 01:53:40,713
Help!

1296
01:53:47,200 --> 01:53:48,952
Kay Chandler, congresswoman.

1297
01:53:49,240 --> 01:53:52,471
Police report said her husband got it on
with Van Den Broeck's wife.

1298
01:53:52,800 --> 01:53:55,030
He kept a love shack in the building.

1299
01:54:02,160 --> 01:54:03,309
You all right?

1300
01:54:05,120 --> 01:54:07,509
The press is out there
and they know you're here.

1301
01:54:07,800 --> 01:54:10,712
They could get hungry
and go somewhere for a hamburger.

1302
01:54:11,000 --> 01:54:12,638
How we gonna handle this?

1303
01:54:13,600 --> 01:54:17,673
"Handle it" is when you got a client
who'll tell you what's going on.

1304
01:54:18,720 --> 01:54:22,190
They'll wanna know just how well
the congresswoman knows the cop.

1305
01:54:22,440 --> 01:54:24,396
- How will we handle this?
- I don't know.

1306
01:54:27,200 --> 01:54:29,839
If we can get back to New Hampshire
and let this age a day...

1307
01:54:30,480 --> 01:54:32,630
We'll leave through the basement.

1308
01:54:33,760 --> 01:54:35,079
He's right, Kay.

1309
01:55:05,080 --> 01:55:06,479
What time is it?

1310
01:55:07,920 --> 01:55:11,230
- It's almost midnight.
- Somebody stole my watch.

1311
01:55:15,280 --> 01:55:16,679
Where's Alcee?

1312
01:55:17,680 --> 01:55:19,671
He said he'd come by tomorrow.

1313
01:55:30,120 --> 01:55:32,270
I was trying to catch up with you.

1314
01:55:34,400 --> 01:55:36,072
What were you going to say?

1315
01:55:37,680 --> 01:55:40,274
I don't know what I was gonna say.
I just...

1316
01:55:41,280 --> 01:55:44,158
I just didn't want you to leave.
Not like that, anyway.

1317
01:55:46,600 --> 01:55:48,397
Welcome back. Hungry?

1318
01:55:48,640 --> 01:55:49,789
Where's my watch?

1319
01:55:50,080 --> 01:55:51,433
They need you in X-ray.

1320
01:55:56,600 --> 01:55:57,874
Listen...

1321
01:56:00,280 --> 01:56:05,070
...I probably never would've told you
about the place either.

1322
01:56:07,240 --> 01:56:08,559
All I wanted...

1323
01:56:10,960 --> 01:56:12,712
What I want, really...

1324
01:56:15,120 --> 01:56:17,270
...is just to find some way...

1325
01:56:18,120 --> 01:56:19,269
...to let her go...

1326
01:56:23,520 --> 01:56:24,919
...and move on.

1327
01:56:27,640 --> 01:56:29,631
I don't know how you do that.

1328
01:56:37,040 --> 01:56:38,519
Neither do I.

1329
01:56:39,800 --> 01:56:41,438
It's not a crime, Dutch.

1330
01:56:42,520 --> 01:56:44,158
You loved your wife.

1331
01:56:47,400 --> 01:56:48,879
And you still do.

1332
01:56:53,360 --> 01:56:55,954
All set. Let me see
if I can find some orderlies.

1333
01:56:57,200 --> 01:56:58,872
Will you hang around?

1334
01:57:02,280 --> 01:57:03,554
I can't.

1335
01:57:03,960 --> 01:57:06,428
You're supposed to be nice.
I've been shot.

1336
01:57:14,800 --> 01:57:16,870
We did okay, Dutch.

1337
01:57:19,920 --> 01:57:21,751
We did the best we could...

1338
01:57:22,560 --> 01:57:24,357
...under the circumstances.

1339
01:57:27,640 --> 01:57:28,959
We ready, sergeant?

1340
01:57:30,080 --> 01:57:32,674
It's time for you to go. Me too.

1341
01:57:36,680 --> 01:57:38,079
Will that be all right?

1342
01:57:47,920 --> 01:57:48,989
So long, Kay.

1343
01:58:00,680 --> 01:58:01,749
Here she comes.

1344
01:58:02,000 --> 01:58:03,991
Can you tell us what you were doing...?

1345
01:58:04,280 --> 01:58:05,793
What's the sergeant's condition?

1346
01:58:06,040 --> 01:58:08,952
I've gotta catch a plane,
but if you can make it short...

1347
01:58:09,480 --> 01:58:13,359
We're told your husband had an affair
with Van Den Broeck's wife.

1348
01:58:13,840 --> 01:58:17,913
They had an apartment, and that's
where you were. Is that correct?

1349
01:58:22,520 --> 01:58:23,839
Yes, it is.

1350
01:58:26,720 --> 01:58:29,393
Characterize your relationship
with the sergeant.

1351
01:58:30,640 --> 01:58:34,872
The sergeant's wife was killed on the
plane that went down with my husband.

1352
01:58:36,080 --> 01:58:39,072
I met the sergeant
a few days after that day.

1353
01:58:40,240 --> 01:58:44,631
He was a friend when I needed a friend.
I hope he feels the same way.

1354
01:58:45,000 --> 01:58:46,479
So you're just friends?

1355
01:58:47,240 --> 01:58:48,912
Just friends.

1356
01:58:50,000 --> 01:58:51,877
We are surely friends.

1357
01:58:53,440 --> 01:58:56,034
We've seen each other
through something...

1358
01:58:56,840 --> 01:58:59,718
We're more than friends.
We're survivors.

1359
01:59:02,760 --> 01:59:05,274
You'll have to excuse me.
I have to get home.

1360
01:59:05,560 --> 01:59:08,472
Can you tell us more
about the sergeant's condition?

1361
01:59:42,480 --> 01:59:45,074
- See you Friday, sweetie.
- Bye, Mom.

1362
02:00:09,080 --> 02:00:10,479
Bye, Mrs. Chandler.

1363
02:00:10,760 --> 02:00:11,829
Merry Christmas.

1364
02:00:12,120 --> 02:00:14,588
Merry Christmas. Do I know you?

1365
02:00:14,840 --> 02:00:17,434
I'm Tad Baker.
I work for Mr. Cornelius.

1366
02:00:18,560 --> 02:00:20,073
You said we could...

1367
02:00:22,000 --> 02:00:24,878
Yeah, sure. Make yourselves at home.

1368
02:01:05,760 --> 02:01:06,749
Hello, Kay.

1369
02:01:07,160 --> 02:01:08,229
Hi, sergeant.

1370
02:01:08,560 --> 02:01:09,709
Lieutenant.

1371
02:01:10,480 --> 02:01:13,597
They made me a lieutenant.
All I had to do was get shot.

1372
02:01:14,880 --> 02:01:17,633
Can I get you something?
Stoli on the rocks.

1373
02:01:18,800 --> 02:01:21,109
I haven't had one of those in a while.

1374
02:01:21,960 --> 02:01:23,473
I got a plane.
I don't have time.

1375
02:01:24,200 --> 02:01:27,397
What's with those New Hampshire voters?
Are they crazy?

1376
02:01:27,840 --> 02:01:30,070
They could tell
I didn't want the job.

1377
02:01:30,400 --> 02:01:33,870
Or I wanted it. I just didn't
wanna do what you have to do to get it.

1378
02:01:36,120 --> 02:01:37,189
So you're out of work.

1379
02:01:38,080 --> 02:01:39,593
Guess I am.

1380
02:01:43,040 --> 02:01:44,598
Are you as well as you look?

1381
02:01:45,920 --> 02:01:47,558
Leg's a little stiff.

1382
02:01:49,800 --> 02:01:52,030
But I think I'm gonna be okay.

1383
02:01:52,720 --> 02:01:53,869
You?

1384
02:01:57,560 --> 02:01:58,993
How's football in Australia?

1385
02:02:01,600 --> 02:02:03,477
I tune in once in a while.

1386
02:02:03,720 --> 02:02:05,472
Not like before.

1387
02:02:06,680 --> 02:02:08,033
I was a real fan.

1388
02:02:12,200 --> 02:02:15,078
I gotta tell you,
I thought I might run into you here.

1389
02:02:15,400 --> 02:02:16,469
Where are you going?

1390
02:02:18,760 --> 02:02:20,273
That's the thing. Nowhere.

1391
02:02:20,560 --> 02:02:23,870
I called your office,
and they said that you were...

1392
02:02:24,200 --> 02:02:26,077
...headed home, so...

1393
02:02:33,920 --> 02:02:35,638
My flight's overbooked and I--

1394
02:02:36,360 --> 02:02:37,190
Go later.

1395
02:02:38,920 --> 02:02:40,512
Take another plane.

1396
02:02:49,560 --> 02:02:52,518
It's my Christmas present,
running into you.

1397
02:03:00,520 --> 02:03:01,748
What'd you get me?

1398
02:03:06,920 --> 02:03:08,273
How about...

1399
02:03:08,880 --> 02:03:11,189
...I call you up sometime
in New Hampshire?

1400
02:03:13,440 --> 02:03:14,873
And say what?

1401
02:03:16,920 --> 02:03:18,273
Say...

1402
02:03:18,960 --> 02:03:20,313
..."You wanna go to a movie?"

1403
02:03:28,120 --> 02:03:29,473
What do you say?

1404
02:03:35,720 --> 02:03:37,551
Wouldn't that be something?

